-- Arsenal, West Ham, Villa Complete Lineup for Carling Cup Quarterfinals
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2010-10-27T22:02:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/arsenal-west-ham-villa-complete-lineup-for-carling-cup-quarterfinals.html
Arsenal beat Newcastle 4-0 while
Aston Villa and West Ham needed extra time to advance to the
quarterfinals of English soccer’s Carling Cup.  Stewart Downing scored to seal a 2-1 victory for Villa
against visitor Burnley. Clarke Carlisle tied it at 1-1 with a
minute of normal time to play, three minutes after Emile Heskey
put Villa ahead.  West Ham got two goals in extra time to beat Stoke 3-1.
Scott Parker scored in the 84th minute for the Hammers after
Kenwyne Jones put Stoke ahead in the sixth minute. Manuel da
Costa and Victor Obinna got West Ham’s goals in extra time.  Theo Walcott got two goals, Nicklas Bendtner also scored
and Newcastle goalkeeper Tim Krul had an own goal at St. James’
Park as Arsenal cruised into the final eight.  Defending champion Manchester United, Wigan, West Brom,
Birmingham and Ipswich had already reached the quarterfinals of
England’s second-tier cup competition.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
